+    "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"tddab\",\n  \"mission\": \"PROJECT: FastAPI web framework (Python >=3.10), built on Starlette 1.0.0 + Pydantic 2. Source lives in `/app/fastapi`. Tests live in `/app/tests` as `test_*.py` and use `from fastapi.testclient import TestClient`. Run tests with `python -m pytest tests/<file> -q` from `/app`.\\n\\nGOAL: Add opt-in implicit `HEAD` (for `GET` routes) and implicit `OPTIONS` (path metadata) handling, controlled by two new boolean parameters `auto_head` (default ON, affects GET routes only) and `auto_options` (default OFF). The parameters are added to: `FastAPI.__init__`, `APIRouter.__init__`, all HTTP-method decorators (`get/put/post/delete/options/head/patch/trace`) on both `FastAPI` and `APIRouter`, `api_route`, `add_api_route`, and `include_router` — on both classes. Public signatures must document the new params with `Annotated[<type>, Doc(\\\"\\\"\\\"...\\\"\\\"\\\")]` (import already present: `from annotated_doc import Doc`).\\n\\nKEY EXISTING MECHANISMS (reuse, do not reinvent):\\n- Sentinel/precedence: `from fastapi.datastructures import Default, DefaultPlaceholder`. `Default(x)` returns a `DefaultPlaceholder` carrying `.value == x`. `from fastapi.utils import get_value_or_default` returns the first non-placeholder argument (else the first placeholder). This is the EXACT analog of the existing `strict_content_type` parameter — mirror it. A stored value is resolved to a concrete bool with: `v.value if isinstance(v, DefaultPlaceholder) else v`.\\n- Routing: `fastapi/routing.py`. `APIRoute(routing.Route)` (line ~807) overrides `__init__` fully; stores `self.methods: set[str]` as UPPERCASE (line ~888; does NOT auto-add HEAD like Starlette does). `self.path_regex, self.path_format, self.param_convertors = compile_path(path)` (line ~885); `path_format` is the route template (e.g. `/items/{item_id}`) and includes any router prefix. `self.app = request_response(self.get_route_handler())` (line ~972). `matches()` (line ~994) sets `child_scope[\\\"route\\\"] = self`.\\n- Dispatch (Starlette `Router.app`): iterates routes; FIRST `Match.FULL` wins and returns; a path-match-but-method-mismatch yields `Match.PARTIAL` (used for 405). So a `GET`-only route returns PARTIAL for a HEAD request, and a separate HEAD-only route returns FULL — correct dispatch. Starlette does NOT auto-generate HEAD or OPTIONS.\\n- `APIRouter.add_api_route` (line ~1332) builds the `APIRoute`, merging router-level tags/deps/callbacks/responses, then `self.routes.append(route)`. `api_route` (line ~1415) is the decorator wrapper. HTTP method decorators each call `self.api_route(..., methods=[\\\"GET\\\"|...])`. `include_router` (line ~1574) re-adds each sub-route via `self.add_api_route(...)` using `get_value_or_default` chains for response_class/strict_content_type/etc.\\n- App: `fastapi/applications.py`. `FastAPI(Starlette)`. `FastAPI.__init__` creates `self.router = routing.APIRouter(...)` (line ~986) forwarding router-level params, and all decorators/`add_api_route`/`api_route`/`include_router` delegate to `self.router`. `app.routes` == `self.router.routes`. `app.openapi()` builds+caches the OpenAPI schema; `paths` keys are `path_format`, method keys are lowercase (`get`,`post`,...). Starlette's `FastAPI.__call__` lazily calls `self.build_middleware_stack()` exactly once on first request (when `self.middleware_stack is None`).\\n- CORS: `CORSMiddleware` (user-added, outer ASGI) short-circuits a true preflight (`method==\\\"OPTIONS\\\"` AND `access-control-request-method` header present) BEFORE routing, so implicit OPTIONS routes never interfere with preflight; non-preflight OPTIONS passes through to our route.\\n\\nPRECEDENCE MODEL (resolve to a concrete bool; the wrapped value inside the placeholder carries the ultimate default — `auto_head -> Default(True)`, `auto_options -> Default(False)`):\\n- Direct app routes: route-level param, else app value (outermost). Implemented because `add_api_route` does `get_value_or_default(param, self.auto_head)` where `self` is the app router whose value defaults to `Default(True)`/`Default(False)`.\\n- Included-router routes: nearest non-omitted among route, include, router — i.e. `get_value_or_default(sub_route.auto_head, include_param, sub_router.auto_head)`, then the including app applies its value as the outer default via `add_api_route`. Order is route > include > router (then app, then ultimate default).\\n- Explicit `HEAD`/`OPTIONS` operations on a path WIN: never synthesize an implicit operation for a (path, method) that already exists.\\n\\nGENERATION (one build pass on the app, idempotent, after all routes are registered): FastAPI already overrides `build_middleware_stack` (applications.py:1021); insert a call to `_setup_implicit_methods()` as the first statement of that existing method (do not add a second override or a `super()` call). The pass scans `self.router.routes`, resolves each route's flags, and appends synthesized routes (with `include_in_schema=False` so OpenAPI output is unchanged). Implicit HEAD: one per GET route whose resolved `auto_head` is True and whose path has no explicit HEAD. Implicit OPTIONS: ONE per path when ANY route on that path has resolved `auto_options` True and the path has no explicit OPTIONS.\\n\\nMETHOD ORDER (canonical, used for `methods` list and `Allow` header): `GET, HEAD, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS, TRACE`.\\n\\nMIDDLEWARE: `fastapi/middleware/methods.py` defines `ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware` (pure ASGI). Implicit route handlers set `scope[\\\"fastapi_implicit_method\\\"] = (\\\"head\\\"|\\\"options\\\", full_path)` (full_path = the route `path_format`). The middleware (outer) reads this marker AFTER awaiting downstream (same scope dict is mutated in place) and increments per-path counters; it ignores non-HTTP scopes. `get_stats()` returns a `copy.deepcopy` of `{full_path: {\\\"head_hits\\\": int, \\\"options_hits\\\": int}}` without mutating; `reset_stats()` returns a deepcopy snapshot of the counts then clears them.\\n\\nCONVENTIONS: keep edits minimal and in the surrounding style. New public params use `Annotated[bool, Doc(\\\"\\\"\\\"...\\\"\\\"\\\")] = Default(True|False)`. Non-public internal `APIRoute.__init__` may use plain `auto_head: bool | DefaultPlaceholder = Default(True)`. Method-order list and helpers live in `fastapi/routing.py`.\",\n  \"sourceFile\": \"plan.md\",\n  \"blocks\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"01-params-and-implicit-head\",\n      \"title\": \"Plumb auto_head/auto_options params and implement implicit HEAD\",\n      \"intro\": \"Adds the two parameters to every signature and wires the generation of implicit HEAD routes end-to-end. Files: `/app/fastapi/routing.py`, `/app/fastapi/applications.py`. After this block, GET routes answer HEAD with status/headers preserved and an empty body, on by default, disable-able, and never overriding an explicit HEAD. `include_router` here forwards `auto_head`/`auto_options` straight to `add_api_route` (full route>include>router resolution is added in block 03). The implicit OPTIONS path stays disabled until block 02 (build pass only handles HEAD here).\",\n      \"red\": \"- `client.head(\\\"/ping\\\")` on `@app.get(\\\"/ping\\\")` returns 200 with empty body (`response.content == b\\\"\\\"`).\\n- implicit HEAD preserves response headers from GET (e.g. a custom header set by the GET endpoint and `content-length` reflecting the GET body length).\\n- implicit HEAD preserves status code (GET declared `status_code=201` -> HEAD returns 201).\\n- implicit HEAD runs the GET dependencies/validation (HEAD with a missing required query param returns 422, not 200).\\n- `auto_head` is on by default — a plain `@app.get` answers HEAD with 200.\\n- `@app.get(\\\"/x\\\", auto_head=False)` -> `client.head(\\\"/x\\\")` returns 405.\\n- `FastAPI(auto_head=False)` disables implicit HEAD for all direct GET routes (HEAD -> 405); a route-level `auto_head=True` re-enables it (route beats app).\\n- a non-GET route (e.g. `@app.post`) never gets an implicit HEAD (HEAD -> 405).\\n- an explicit `@app.head(\\\"/x\\\")` wins — its handler runs (returns its own body), no implicit HEAD is synthesized.\\n- implicit HEAD route is excluded from OpenAPI (`app.openapi()[\\\"paths\\\"][\\\"/ping\\\"]` has no `head` key).\",\n      \"redKeys\": [\n        \"clientheadping_on_appgetping_returns_200\",\n        \"implicit_head_preserves_response_headers\",\n        \"implicit_head_preserves_status_code_get\",\n        \"implicit_head_runs_the_get_dependenciesv\",\n        \"autohead_is_on_by_default_a_plain_appge\",\n        \"appgetx_autoheadfalse_clientheadx_retur\",\n        \"fastapiautoheadfalse_disables_implicit_h\",\n        \"a_nonget_route_eg_apppost_never_gets_an\",\n        \"an_explicit_appheadx_wins_its_handler_r\",\n        \"implicit_head_route_is_excluded_from_ope\"\n      ],\n      \"success\": \"- [ ] All 10 RED tests pass.\\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/test_application.py tests/test_extra_routes.py -q` still passes (no regressions to explicit routes/OpenAPI).\\n- [ ] New params appear in `FastAPI`, `APIRouter`, their decorators, `api_route`, `add_api_route`, `include_router` with `Annotated[..., Doc(...)]`.\\n- [ ] Implicit HEAD routes carry `include_in_schema=False` and `methods == {\\\"HEAD\\\"}`.\",\n      \"planRef\": \"See plan.md lines 31-155\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"02-implicit-options\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement implicit OPTIONS path-metadata responses\",\n      \"intro\": \"Adds implicit OPTIONS generation: one synthesized OPTIONS route per path when any operation on that path has `auto_options` True and no explicit OPTIONS exists. Files: `/app/fastapi/routing.py`, `/app/fastapi/applications.py`. Depends on block 01 (params, build pass, `_resolve_implicit_flag`, method-order constant). The OPTIONS handler returns 200 JSON with `path`, ordered `methods`, and `operations` (the OpenAPI path item minus head/options), and sends an `Allow` header.\",\n      \"red\": \"- with `@app.get(\\\"/m\\\", auto_options=True)`, `client.options(\\\"/m\\\")` returns 200 and JSON has keys `path`, `methods`, `operations`.\\n- response `path` equals the route template (`/m`); for a parametrized path `/items/{item_id}` it equals `/items/{item_id}`.\\n- `methods` is ordered per `GET, HEAD, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS, TRACE` (e.g. a path with POST+GET+auto_head+auto_options yields `[\\\"GET\\\",\\\"HEAD\\\",\\\"POST\\\",\\\"OPTIONS\\\"]`).\\n- `Allow` response header equals `\\\", \\\".join(methods)`.\\n- `operations` excludes `head` and `options` keys and equals the GET/POST/... entries from `app.openapi()[\\\"paths\\\"][path]`.\\n- `auto_options` is OFF by default — `client.options(\\\"/d\\\")` on a plain `@app.get(\\\"/d\\\")` returns 405.\\n- exactly ONE implicit OPTIONS per path even when multiple operations on it enable it (no duplicate route; second registration via another method with `auto_options=True` does not add a second OPTIONS).\\n- `FastAPI(auto_options=True)` enables OPTIONS for all paths; a route-level `auto_options=False` disables it for that path.\\n- an explicit `@app.options(\\\"/x\\\")` wins — implicit OPTIONS is not synthesized and the explicit handler runs.\\n- implicit OPTIONS route is excluded from OpenAPI (no `options` key under its path).\\n- CORS preflight still works — with `CORSMiddleware` added and `auto_options=True`, an OPTIONS request carrying `Origin` + `Access-Control-Request-Method` returns the CORS preflight response (200 with `access-control-allow-*` headers), not the metadata JSON.\",\n      \"redKeys\": [\n        \"with_appgetm_autooptionstrue_clientoptio\",\n        \"response_path_equals_the_route_template\",\n        \"methods_is_ordered_per_get_head_post_put\",\n        \"allow_response_header_equals_joinmethod\",\n        \"operations_excludes_head_and_options_key\",\n        \"autooptions_is_off_by_default_clientopt\",\n        \"exactly_one_implicit_options_per_path_ev\",\n        \"fastapiautooptionstrue_enables_options_f\",\n        \"an_explicit_appoptionsx_wins_implicit_o\",\n        \"implicit_options_route_is_excluded_from\",\n        \"cors_preflight_still_works_with_corsmid\"\n      ],\n      \"success\": \"- [ ] All 11 RED tests pass.\\n- [ ] `operations` content is byte-for-byte the `app.openapi()` path item minus head/options.\\n- [ ] Only one OPTIONS route exists per path in `app.routes`.\\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/test_application.py -q` passes (OpenAPI output unaffected).\",\n      \"planRef\": \"See plan.md lines 157-248\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"03-include-router-precedence\",\n      \"title\": \"Resolve include_router precedence (route > include > router) and repeated inclusion\",\n      \"intro\": \"Upgrades `include_router` (both `APIRouter` and, by delegation, `FastAPI`) so included sub-routes resolve `auto_head`/`auto_options` by nearest non-omitted setting among route, include, and router — then the including app applies its value as the outer default. Files: `/app/fastapi/routing.py` only — `FastAPI.include_router` already forwards the params to `self.router.include_router` (added in block 01), so applications.py needs no change here. Depends on blocks 01 and 02. Verifies repeated and nested inclusion.\",\n      \"red\": \"- sub-router route `@r.get(\\\"/a\\\", auto_options=True)`; `app.include_router(r)` -> OPTIONS `/a` is implicit (route-level wins, 200).\\n- include-level `app.include_router(r, auto_options=True)` enables OPTIONS for sub-routes that omit it (200), while a sub-route with explicit `auto_options=False` stays disabled (405) — route beats include.\\n- router-level `APIRouter(auto_options=True)` enables OPTIONS for its routes when include and route omit it (200); an include-level `auto_options=False` overrides the router-level for omitted routes (405) — include beats router.\\n- route-level `auto_head=False` on a sub-router GET survives inclusion (HEAD -> 405) even when include and router leave it default.\\n- repeated inclusion — `app.include_router(r, prefix=\\\"/x\\\")` and `app.include_router(r, prefix=\\\"/y\\\")` each independently get correct implicit HEAD/OPTIONS at `/x/...` and `/y/...`.\\n- nested inclusion — `outer.include_router(inner)` then `app.include_router(outer)`; the nearest-set value (inner route/include) is honored for HEAD/OPTIONS.\\n- app value as outer default still applies to included routes that omit at all three levels (`FastAPI(auto_options=True)` + plain sub-route -> OPTIONS 200).\",\n      \"redKeys\": [\n        \"subrouter_route_rgeta_autooptionstrue_ap\",\n        \"includelevel_appincluderouterr_autooptio\",\n        \"routerlevel_apirouterautooptionstrue_ena\",\n        \"routelevel_autoheadfalse_on_a_subrouter\",\n        \"repeated_inclusion_appincluderouterr_pr\",\n        \"nested_inclusion_outerincluderouterinne\",\n        \"app_value_as_outer_default_still_applies\"\n      ],\n      \"success\": \"- [ ] All 7 RED tests pass.\\n- [ ] Precedence order is route > include > router > app(outer) > ultimate default, verified per layer.\\n- [ ] Repeated inclusion produces independent, correct implicit routes per prefix.\\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/test_router_events.py tests/test_application.py -q` passes.\",\n      \"planRef\": \"See plan.md lines 250-282\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"04-tracking-middleware-and-verification\",\n      \"title\": \"ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware and consolidated verification\",\n      \"intro\": \"Adds `ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware` in the new file `/app/fastapi/middleware/methods.py`, reading the `scope[\\\"fastapi_implicit_method\\\"]` markers set by the implicit HEAD/OPTIONS handlers (blocks 01/02). Also consolidates the docs-surface / OpenAPI-output verification. Files: `/app/fastapi/middleware/methods.py` (new), plus verification tests. Depends on blocks 01–03.\",\n      \"red\": \"- after one implicit `HEAD /p` hit, `mw.get_stats() == {\\\"/p\\\": {\\\"head_hits\\\": 1, \\\"options_hits\\\": 0}}`.\\n- after one implicit `OPTIONS /p` hit (auto_options on), stats show `{\\\"/p\\\": {\\\"head_hits\\\": 0, \\\"options_hits\\\": 1}}`; counts accumulate across multiple hits.\\n- explicit routes are NOT counted — an explicit `@app.head`/`@app.options` hit leaves stats empty for that path.\\n- a normal `GET` hit does not change stats.\\n- `get_stats()` returns a deep copy — mutating the returned dict does not affect subsequent `get_stats()`.\\n- `reset_stats()` clears counts (subsequent `get_stats()` returns `{}`) and returns a deepcopy snapshot of the pre-clear counts.\\n- non-HTTP scopes are ignored — a websocket/lifespan request does not raise and does not create stats entries.\\n- implicit HEAD and implicit OPTIONS routes do not appear in `app.openapi()` paths (OpenAPI output unchanged vs a baseline app without the flags for the real operations).\\n- the `auto_head`/`auto_options` parameters are present in the rendered signatures `inspect.signature(FastAPI.get).parameters` and `inspect.signature(APIRouter.__init__).parameters` so the docs surface exposes them.\",\n      \"redKeys\": [\n        \"after_one_implicit_head_p_hit_mwgetstats\",\n        \"after_one_implicit_options_p_hit_autoopt\",\n        \"explicit_routes_are_not_counted_an_expl\",\n        \"a_normal_get_hit_does_not_change_stats\",\n        \"getstats_returns_a_deep_copy_mutating_t\",\n        \"resetstats_clears_counts_subsequent_gets\",\n        \"nonhttp_scopes_are_ignored_a_websocketl\",\n        \"implicit_head_and_implicit_options_route\",\n        \"the_autoheadautooptions_parameters_are_p\"\n      ],\n      \"success\": \"- [ ] All 9 RED tests pass.\\n- [ ] `get_stats()`/`reset_stats()` return independent deep copies shaped `{full_path: {\\\"head_hits\\\": int, \\\"options_hits\\\": int}}`.\\n- [ ] Only implicit hits are tracked; explicit and normal hits are ignored; non-HTTP scopes pass through untouched.\\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/ -q` passes with no regressions.\",\n      \"planRef\": \"See plan.md lines 284-346\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
