+# TDDAB Plan: Implicit HEAD & OPTIONS for FastAPI
+**Date:** 2026-05-31
+
+<mission>
+PROJECT: FastAPI web framework (Python >=3.10), built on Starlette 1.0.0 + Pydantic 2. Source lives in `/app/fastapi`. Tests live in `/app/tests` as `test_*.py` and use `from fastapi.testclient import TestClient`. Run tests with `python -m pytest tests/<file> -q` from `/app`.
+
+GOAL: Add opt-in implicit `HEAD` (for `GET` routes) and implicit `OPTIONS` (path metadata) handling, controlled by two new boolean parameters `auto_head` (default ON, affects GET routes only) and `auto_options` (default OFF). The parameters are added to: `FastAPI.__init__`, `APIRouter.__init__`, all HTTP-method decorators (`get/put/post/delete/options/head/patch/trace`) on both `FastAPI` and `APIRouter`, `api_route`, `add_api_route`, and `include_router` — on both classes. Public signatures must document the new params with `Annotated[<type>, Doc("""...""")]` (import already present: `from annotated_doc import Doc`).
+
+KEY EXISTING MECHANISMS (reuse, do not reinvent):
+- Sentinel/precedence: `from fastapi.datastructures import Default, DefaultPlaceholder`. `Default(x)` returns a `DefaultPlaceholder` carrying `.value == x`. `from fastapi.utils import get_value_or_default` returns the first non-placeholder argument (else the first placeholder). This is the EXACT analog of the existing `strict_content_type` parameter — mirror it. A stored value is resolved to a concrete bool with: `v.value if isinstance(v, DefaultPlaceholder) else v`.
+- Routing: `fastapi/routing.py`. `APIRoute(routing.Route)` (line ~807) overrides `__init__` fully; stores `self.methods: set[str]` as UPPERCASE (line ~888; does NOT auto-add HEAD like Starlette does). `self.path_regex, self.path_format, self.param_convertors = compile_path(path)` (line ~885); `path_format` is the route template (e.g. `/items/{item_id}`) and includes any router prefix. `self.app = request_response(self.get_route_handler())` (line ~972). `matches()` (line ~994) sets `child_scope["route"] = self`.
+- Dispatch (Starlette `Router.app`): iterates routes; FIRST `Match.FULL` wins and returns; a path-match-but-method-mismatch yields `Match.PARTIAL` (used for 405). So a `GET`-only route returns PARTIAL for a HEAD request, and a separate HEAD-only route returns FULL — correct dispatch. Starlette does NOT auto-generate HEAD or OPTIONS.
+- `APIRouter.add_api_route` (line ~1332) builds the `APIRoute`, merging router-level tags/deps/callbacks/responses, then `self.routes.append(route)`. `api_route` (line ~1415) is the decorator wrapper. HTTP method decorators each call `self.api_route(..., methods=["GET"|...])`. `include_router` (line ~1574) re-adds each sub-route via `self.add_api_route(...)` using `get_value_or_default` chains for response_class/strict_content_type/etc.
+- App: `fastapi/applications.py`. `FastAPI(Starlette)`. `FastAPI.__init__` creates `self.router = routing.APIRouter(...)` (line ~986) forwarding router-level params, and all decorators/`add_api_route`/`api_route`/`include_router` delegate to `self.router`. `app.routes` == `self.router.routes`. `app.openapi()` builds+caches the OpenAPI schema; `paths` keys are `path_format`, method keys are lowercase (`get`,`post`,...). Starlette's `FastAPI.__call__` lazily calls `self.build_middleware_stack()` exactly once on first request (when `self.middleware_stack is None`).
+- CORS: `CORSMiddleware` (user-added, outer ASGI) short-circuits a true preflight (`method=="OPTIONS"` AND `access-control-request-method` header present) BEFORE routing, so implicit OPTIONS routes never interfere with preflight; non-preflight OPTIONS passes through to our route.
+
+PRECEDENCE MODEL (resolve to a concrete bool; the wrapped value inside the placeholder carries the ultimate default — `auto_head -> Default(True)`, `auto_options -> Default(False)`):
+- Direct app routes: route-level param, else app value (outermost). Implemented because `add_api_route` does `get_value_or_default(param, self.auto_head)` where `self` is the app router whose value defaults to `Default(True)`/`Default(False)`.
+- Included-router routes: nearest non-omitted among route, include, router — i.e. `get_value_or_default(sub_route.auto_head, include_param, sub_router.auto_head)`, then the including app applies its value as the outer default via `add_api_route`. Order is route > include > router (then app, then ultimate default).
+- Explicit `HEAD`/`OPTIONS` operations on a path WIN: never synthesize an implicit operation for a (path, method) that already exists.
+
+GENERATION (one build pass on the app, idempotent, after all routes are registered): FastAPI already overrides `build_middleware_stack` (applications.py:1021); insert a call to `_setup_implicit_methods()` as the first statement of that existing method (do not add a second override or a `super()` call). The pass scans `self.router.routes`, resolves each route's flags, and appends synthesized routes (with `include_in_schema=False` so OpenAPI output is unchanged). Implicit HEAD: one per GET route whose resolved `auto_head` is True and whose path has no explicit HEAD. Implicit OPTIONS: ONE per path when ANY route on that path has resolved `auto_options` True and the path has no explicit OPTIONS.
+
+METHOD ORDER (canonical, used for `methods` list and `Allow` header): `GET, HEAD, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS, TRACE`.
+
+MIDDLEWARE: `fastapi/middleware/methods.py` defines `ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware` (pure ASGI). Implicit route handlers set `scope["fastapi_implicit_method"] = ("head"|"options", full_path)` (full_path = the route `path_format`). The middleware (outer) reads this marker AFTER awaiting downstream (same scope dict is mutated in place) and increments per-path counters; it ignores non-HTTP scopes. `get_stats()` returns a `copy.deepcopy` of `{full_path: {"head_hits": int, "options_hits": int}}` without mutating; `reset_stats()` returns a deepcopy snapshot of the counts then clears them.
+
+CONVENTIONS: keep edits minimal and in the surrounding style. New public params use `Annotated[bool, Doc("""...""")] = Default(True|False)`. Non-public internal `APIRoute.__init__` may use plain `auto_head: bool | DefaultPlaceholder = Default(True)`. Method-order list and helpers live in `fastapi/routing.py`.
+</mission>
+
+<block id="01-params-and-implicit-head">
+## TDDAB-1: Plumb auto_head/auto_options params and implement implicit HEAD
+
+<intro>
+Adds the two parameters to every signature and wires the generation of implicit HEAD routes end-to-end. Files: `/app/fastapi/routing.py`, `/app/fastapi/applications.py`. After this block, GET routes answer HEAD with status/headers preserved and an empty body, on by default, disable-able, and never overriding an explicit HEAD. `include_router` here forwards `auto_head`/`auto_options` straight to `add_api_route` (full route>include>router resolution is added in block 03). The implicit OPTIONS path stays disabled until block 02 (build pass only handles HEAD here).
+</intro>
+
+<red>
+- test: `client.head("/ping")` on `@app.get("/ping")` returns 200 with empty body (`response.content == b""`).
+- test: implicit HEAD preserves response headers from GET (e.g. a custom header set by the GET endpoint and `content-length` reflecting the GET body length).
+- test: implicit HEAD preserves status code (GET declared `status_code=201` -> HEAD returns 201).
+- test: implicit HEAD runs the GET dependencies/validation (HEAD with a missing required query param returns 422, not 200).
+- test: `auto_head` is on by default — a plain `@app.get` answers HEAD with 200.
+- test: `@app.get("/x", auto_head=False)` -> `client.head("/x")` returns 405.
+- test: `FastAPI(auto_head=False)` disables implicit HEAD for all direct GET routes (HEAD -> 405); a route-level `auto_head=True` re-enables it (route beats app).
+- test: a non-GET route (e.g. `@app.post`) never gets an implicit HEAD (HEAD -> 405).
+- test: an explicit `@app.head("/x")` wins — its handler runs (returns its own body), no implicit HEAD is synthesized.
+- test: implicit HEAD route is excluded from OpenAPI (`app.openapi()["paths"]["/ping"]` has no `head` key).
+</red>
+
+### Implementation
+
+In `/app/fastapi/routing.py`:
+
+Add module-level constant near other constants:
+```python
+IMPLICIT_HTTP_METHOD_ORDER = ["GET", "HEAD", "POST", "PUT", "PATCH", "DELETE", "OPTIONS", "TRACE"]
+
+def _resolve_implicit_flag(value: "bool | DefaultPlaceholder") -> bool:
+    return bool(value.value) if isinstance(value, DefaultPlaceholder) else bool(value)
+```
+
+`APIRoute.__init__`: add params `auto_head: bool | DefaultPlaceholder = Default(True)` and `auto_options: bool | DefaultPlaceholder = Default(False)`; store `self.auto_head = auto_head` and `self.auto_options = auto_options` (next to `self.strict_content_type`).
+
+Add the HEAD subclass after `APIRoute`:
+```python
+class ImplicitHeadRoute(APIRoute):
+    """HEAD route synthesized from a GET route: runs the GET handler, drops the body."""
+    def __init__(self, source: APIRoute) -> None:
+        super().__init__(
+            source.path,
+            source.endpoint,
+            response_model=source.response_model,
+            status_code=source.status_code,
+            tags=list(source.tags),
+            dependencies=list(source.dependencies),
+            summary=source.summary,
+            description=source.description,
+            response_description=source.response_description,
+            responses=dict(source.responses),
+            deprecated=source.deprecated,
+            name=source.name,
+            methods=["HEAD"],
+            operation_id=source.operation_id,
+            response_model_include=source.response_model_include,
+            response_model_exclude=source.response_model_exclude,
+            response_model_by_alias=source.response_model_by_alias,
+            response_model_exclude_unset=source.response_model_exclude_unset,
+            response_model_exclude_defaults=source.response_model_exclude_defaults,
+            response_model_exclude_none=source.response_model_exclude_none,
+            include_in_schema=False,
+            response_class=source.response_class,
+            dependency_overrides_provider=source.dependency_overrides_provider,
+            callbacks=source.callbacks,
+            openapi_extra=source.openapi_extra,
+            generate_unique_id_function=source.generate_unique_id_function,
+            strict_content_type=source.strict_content_type,
+        )
+
+    def get_route_handler(self) -> Callable[[Request], Coroutine[Any, Any, Response]]:
+        handler = super().get_route_handler()
+        async def head_handler(request: Request) -> Response:
+            request.scope["fastapi_implicit_method"] = ("head", self.path_format)
+            response = await handler(request)
+            if hasattr(response, "body"):
+                response.body = b""  # preserve status + headers (incl content-length); no body
+            return response
+        return head_handler
+```
+
+Thread `auto_head`/`auto_options` through `add_api_route`, `api_route`, and every HTTP-method decorator in `APIRouter`, using `Annotated[bool, Doc("""...""")] = Default(True|False)`. In `APIRouter.__init__` add the params and `self.auto_head = auto_head`, `self.auto_options = auto_options`. In `add_api_route`, resolve against the router and pass to the `APIRoute(...)` call:
+```python
+auto_head=get_value_or_default(auto_head, self.auto_head),
+auto_options=get_value_or_default(auto_options, self.auto_options),
+```
+`api_route` and the method decorators forward the params unchanged to `add_api_route`. `include_router` (this block) gains the two params and forwards them directly: `auto_head=auto_head, auto_options=auto_options` to `add_api_route` (refined in block 03).
+
+In `/app/fastapi/applications.py`:
+
+`FastAPI.__init__`: add `auto_head`/`auto_options` params (Annotated+Doc, defaults `Default(True)`/`Default(False)`) and forward into `self.router = routing.APIRouter(..., auto_head=auto_head, auto_options=auto_options)`. Add the same params (Annotated+Doc) to FastAPI's `add_api_route`, `api_route`, every HTTP-method decorator, and `include_router`, forwarding each to the corresponding `self.router.*` call.
+
+Add the build pass. FastAPI already overrides `build_middleware_stack` (line ~1021, the `# Duplicate/override from Starlette...` method) — insert `self._setup_implicit_methods()` as the FIRST statement of that existing method (do NOT add a second override). Then add the helper method:
+```python
+# first line inside the existing FastAPI.build_middleware_stack:
+#     self._setup_implicit_methods()
+
+def _setup_implicit_methods(self) -> None:
+    if getattr(self, "_implicit_methods_built", False):
+        return
+    self._implicit_methods_built = True
+    routes = self.router.routes
+    methods_by_path: dict[str, set] = {}
+    for route in routes:
+        if isinstance(route, routing.APIRoute):
+            methods_by_path.setdefault(route.path_format, set()).update(route.methods)
+    new_routes: list = []
+    head_done: set = set()
+    for route in list(routes):
+        if not isinstance(route, routing.APIRoute):
+            continue
+        if "GET" in route.methods and routing._resolve_implicit_flag(route.auto_head):
+            pf = route.path_format
+            if "HEAD" not in methods_by_path.get(pf, set()) and pf not in head_done:
+                new_routes.append(routing.ImplicitHeadRoute(route))
+                head_done.add(pf)
+    self.router.routes.extend(new_routes)
+```
+
