+<block id="02-implicit-options">
+## TDDAB-2: Implement implicit OPTIONS path-metadata responses
+
+<intro>
+Adds implicit OPTIONS generation: one synthesized OPTIONS route per path when any operation on that path has `auto_options` True and no explicit OPTIONS exists. Files: `/app/fastapi/routing.py`, `/app/fastapi/applications.py`. Depends on block 01 (params, build pass, `_resolve_implicit_flag`, method-order constant). The OPTIONS handler returns 200 JSON with `path`, ordered `methods`, and `operations` (the OpenAPI path item minus head/options), and sends an `Allow` header.
+</intro>
+
+<red>
+- test: with `@app.get("/m", auto_options=True)`, `client.options("/m")` returns 200 and JSON has keys `path`, `methods`, `operations`.
+- test: response `path` equals the route template (`/m`); for a parametrized path `/items/{item_id}` it equals `/items/{item_id}`.
+- test: `methods` is ordered per `GET, HEAD, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS, TRACE` (e.g. a path with POST+GET+auto_head+auto_options yields `["GET","HEAD","POST","OPTIONS"]`).
+- test: `Allow` response header equals `", ".join(methods)`.
+- test: `operations` excludes `head` and `options` keys and equals the GET/POST/... entries from `app.openapi()["paths"][path]`.
+- test: `auto_options` is OFF by default — `client.options("/d")` on a plain `@app.get("/d")` returns 405.
+- test: exactly ONE implicit OPTIONS per path even when multiple operations on it enable it (no duplicate route; second registration via another method with `auto_options=True` does not add a second OPTIONS).
+- test: `FastAPI(auto_options=True)` enables OPTIONS for all paths; a route-level `auto_options=False` disables it for that path.
+- test: an explicit `@app.options("/x")` wins — implicit OPTIONS is not synthesized and the explicit handler runs.
+- test: implicit OPTIONS route is excluded from OpenAPI (no `options` key under its path).
+- test: CORS preflight still works — with `CORSMiddleware` added and `auto_options=True`, an OPTIONS request carrying `Origin` + `Access-Control-Request-Method` returns the CORS preflight response (200 with `access-control-allow-*` headers), not the metadata JSON.
+</red>
+
+### Implementation
+
+In `/app/fastapi/routing.py` add helpers and the OPTIONS subclass:
+```python
+def _ordered_methods_for_path(app: Any, full_path: str) -> list[str]:
+    served: set[str] = set()
+    for route in app.router.routes:
+        if isinstance(route, APIRoute) and route.path_format == full_path:
+            served |= route.methods
+    return [m for m in IMPLICIT_HTTP_METHOD_ORDER if m in served]
+
+def _build_implicit_options_response(request: Request, full_path: str) -> Response:
+    request.scope["fastapi_implicit_method"] = ("options", full_path)
+    methods = _ordered_methods_for_path(request.app, full_path)
+    try:
+        schema = request.app.openapi()
+    except Exception:
+        schema = {}
+    path_item = (schema.get("paths") or {}).get(full_path, {})
+    operations = {
+        method: op
+        for method, op in path_item.items()
+        if method.lower() not in ("head", "options")
+    }
+    content = {
+        "path": full_path,
+        "methods": methods,
+        "operations": jsonable_encoder(operations),
+    }
+    return JSONResponse(
+        content=content, status_code=200, headers={"Allow": ", ".join(methods)}
+    )
+
+class ImplicitOptionsRoute(APIRoute):
+    """One synthesized OPTIONS route per path exposing path metadata."""
+    def __init__(self, path: str) -> None:
+        async def implicit_options_endpoint(request: Request) -> Response:
+            return _build_implicit_options_response(request, self.path_format)
+        super().__init__(
+            path,
+            implicit_options_endpoint,
+            methods=["OPTIONS"],
+            include_in_schema=False,
+            name="implicit_options",
+        )
+```
+(`jsonable_encoder` is already imported in routing.py.)
+
+In `/app/fastapi/applications.py` extend `_setup_implicit_methods` (before `self.router.routes.extend(new_routes)`):
+```python
+    options_paths: dict[str, str] = {}  # path_format -> route.path (template incl prefix)
+    for route in list(routes):
+        if not isinstance(route, routing.APIRoute):
+            continue
+        if routing._resolve_implicit_flag(route.auto_options):
+            options_paths.setdefault(route.path_format, route.path)
+    options_done: set = set()
+    for pf, path in options_paths.items():
+        if "OPTIONS" not in methods_by_path.get(pf, set()) and pf not in options_done:
+            new_routes.append(routing.ImplicitOptionsRoute(path))
+            options_done.add(pf)
+```
+Note: append HEAD routes first then OPTIONS so the OPTIONS handler's `_ordered_methods_for_path` (computed at request time) sees the synthesized HEAD too.
+
+<success>
+- [ ] All 11 RED tests pass.
+- [ ] `operations` content is byte-for-byte the `app.openapi()` path item minus head/options.
+- [ ] Only one OPTIONS route exists per path in `app.routes`.
+- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/test_application.py -q` passes (OpenAPI output unaffected).
+</success>
+</block>
