+<block id="03-include-router-precedence">
+## TDDAB-3: Resolve include_router precedence (route > include > router) and repeated inclusion
+
+<intro>
+Upgrades `include_router` (both `APIRouter` and, by delegation, `FastAPI`) so included sub-routes resolve `auto_head`/`auto_options` by nearest non-omitted setting among route, include, and router — then the including app applies its value as the outer default. Files: `/app/fastapi/routing.py` only — `FastAPI.include_router` already forwards the params to `self.router.include_router` (added in block 01), so applications.py needs no change here. Depends on blocks 01 and 02. Verifies repeated and nested inclusion.
+</intro>
+
+<red>
+- test: sub-router route `@r.get("/a", auto_options=True)`; `app.include_router(r)` -> OPTIONS `/a` is implicit (route-level wins, 200).
+- test: include-level `app.include_router(r, auto_options=True)` enables OPTIONS for sub-routes that omit it (200), while a sub-route with explicit `auto_options=False` stays disabled (405) — route beats include.
+- test: router-level `APIRouter(auto_options=True)` enables OPTIONS for its routes when include and route omit it (200); an include-level `auto_options=False` overrides the router-level for omitted routes (405) — include beats router.
+- test: route-level `auto_head=False` on a sub-router GET survives inclusion (HEAD -> 405) even when include and router leave it default.
+- test: repeated inclusion — `app.include_router(r, prefix="/x")` and `app.include_router(r, prefix="/y")` each independently get correct implicit HEAD/OPTIONS at `/x/...` and `/y/...`.
+- test: nested inclusion — `outer.include_router(inner)` then `app.include_router(outer)`; the nearest-set value (inner route/include) is honored for HEAD/OPTIONS.
+- test: app value as outer default still applies to included routes that omit at all three levels (`FastAPI(auto_options=True)` + plain sub-route -> OPTIONS 200).
+</red>
+
+### Implementation
+
+In `/app/fastapi/routing.py` `include_router`, inside the `isinstance(route, APIRoute)` branch, replace the direct forwarding with resolution against the three levels (mirrors the existing `strict_content_type` resolution but with order route, include, router):
+```python
+current_auto_head = get_value_or_default(route.auto_head, auto_head, router.auto_head)
+current_auto_options = get_value_or_default(route.auto_options, auto_options, router.auto_options)
+```
+Pass `auto_head=current_auto_head, auto_options=current_auto_options` to `self.add_api_route(...)`. `add_api_route` then applies `get_value_or_default(current_auto_head, self.auto_head)` so the including app/router supplies the outer default; if everything is omitted the wrapped ultimate default (`Default(True)`/`Default(False)`) is resolved by `_resolve_implicit_flag` in the build pass. `FastAPI.include_router` already forwards `auto_head`/`auto_options` to `self.router.include_router` (added in block 01), so no change to applications.py is required in this block.
+
+<success>
+- [ ] All 7 RED tests pass.
+- [ ] Precedence order is route > include > router > app(outer) > ultimate default, verified per layer.
+- [ ] Repeated inclusion produces independent, correct implicit routes per prefix.
+- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/test_router_events.py tests/test_application.py -q` passes.
+</success>
