+<block id="04-tracking-middleware-and-verification">
+## TDDAB-4: ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware and consolidated verification
+
+<intro>
+Adds `ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware` in the new file `/app/fastapi/middleware/methods.py`, reading the `scope["fastapi_implicit_method"]` markers set by the implicit HEAD/OPTIONS handlers (blocks 01/02). Also consolidates the docs-surface / OpenAPI-output verification. Files: `/app/fastapi/middleware/methods.py` (new), plus verification tests. Depends on blocks 01–03.
+</intro>
+
+<red>
+- test: after one implicit `HEAD /p` hit, `mw.get_stats() == {"/p": {"head_hits": 1, "options_hits": 0}}`.
+- test: after one implicit `OPTIONS /p` hit (auto_options on), stats show `{"/p": {"head_hits": 0, "options_hits": 1}}`; counts accumulate across multiple hits.
+- test: explicit routes are NOT counted — an explicit `@app.head`/`@app.options` hit leaves stats empty for that path.
+- test: a normal `GET` hit does not change stats.
+- test: `get_stats()` returns a deep copy — mutating the returned dict does not affect subsequent `get_stats()`.
+- test: `reset_stats()` clears counts (subsequent `get_stats()` returns `{}`) and returns a deepcopy snapshot of the pre-clear counts.
+- test: non-HTTP scopes are ignored — a websocket/lifespan request does not raise and does not create stats entries.
+- test: implicit HEAD and implicit OPTIONS routes do not appear in `app.openapi()` paths (OpenAPI output unchanged vs a baseline app without the flags for the real operations).
+- test: the `auto_head`/`auto_options` parameters are present in the rendered signatures `inspect.signature(FastAPI.get).parameters` and `inspect.signature(APIRouter.__init__).parameters` so the docs surface exposes them.
+</red>
+
+### Implementation
+
+Create `/app/fastapi/middleware/methods.py`:
+```python
+import copy
+from starlette.types import ASGIApp, Receive, Scope, Send
+
+class ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware:
+    def __init__(self, app: ASGIApp) -> None:
+        self.app = app
+        self._stats: dict[str, dict[str, int]] = {}
+
+    async def __call__(self, scope: Scope, receive: Receive, send: Send) -> None:
+        if scope["type"] != "http":
+            await self.app(scope, receive, send)
+            return
+        await self.app(scope, receive, send)
+        marker = scope.get("fastapi_implicit_method")
+        if not marker:
+            return
+        kind, full_path = marker
+        entry = self._stats.setdefault(full_path, {"head_hits": 0, "options_hits": 0})
+        if kind == "head":
+            entry["head_hits"] += 1
+        elif kind == "options":
+            entry["options_hits"] += 1
+
+    def get_stats(self) -> dict[str, dict[str, int]]:
+        return copy.deepcopy(self._stats)
+
+    def reset_stats(self) -> dict[str, dict[str, int]]:
+        snapshot = copy.deepcopy(self._stats)
+        self._stats = {}
+        return snapshot
+```
+Drive the middleware in tests by constructing `mw = ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware(app)` and wrapping it with `TestClient(mw)`, then assert on `mw.get_stats()` / `mw.reset_stats()`. The implicit handlers already set the `scope["fastapi_implicit_method"]` marker; no change to routing is needed.
+
+<success>
+- [ ] All 9 RED tests pass.
+- [ ] `get_stats()`/`reset_stats()` return independent deep copies shaped `{full_path: {"head_hits": int, "options_hits": int}}`.
+- [ ] Only implicit hits are tracked; explicit and normal hits are ignored; non-HTTP scopes pass through untouched.
+- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/ -q` passes with no regressions.
+</success>
